Communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Data by country, area, or territory for 14 May 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20May14_1621106795.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 27.1% of daily case numbers and 40.7% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 64.34 million cases. Brazil reported over 76 000 cases over the last 24 hours followed by the USA with 35 437 cases, Argentina (24 475), and Columbia (16 993). 10 additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours (Canada, Peru, Mexico, Costa Rica, Paraguay, Uruguay, Chile, Bolivia, Ecuador, and Cuba). 6 additional countries (Dominican Republic, Honduras, Panama, El Salvador, Trinidad and Tobago, and Venezuela) reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 13.7% of daily case numbers and 17.7% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 53.37 million cases. Many countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Spain, Belgium (2 cases), Switzerland, and Kazakhstan, among others. France reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours followed by Turkey and Germany, each reporting more than 10 000 new cases in the past 24 hours. Another 13 countries reported more than 1000 cases, and an additional 8 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 4.4 % of daily case numbers and 5.1% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 9.60 million cases. Iran reported the highest number of cases (14 246) over the last 24 hours, followed by Iraq, Pakistan, Bahrain, UAE, Egypt, Saudi Arabia, and Kuwait. Lebanon and Tunisia reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 1.3% of daily case numbers and 0.8 % of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 3.38 million cases. South Africa (3221) reported the highest number of cases over last 24 hours followed by Botswana (2497) and Seychelles (1012). Ethiopia (593) reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Cameroon, Congo, and Mali, among others, did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 2.8% of daily case numbers and 1.8% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 2.69 million cases. Japan reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 6900 cases), followed by Philippines, Malaysia, South Korea, and Mongolia.

- The South East Asia region reported 50.7% of the daily newly reported cases and 33.7% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 27.40 million cases. India is dominant, reporting over 343 000 cases, followed by Nepal (8842), Indonesia (3448), Sri Lanka (3269), Thailand (2256), Bangladesh (1290), and Maldives (1216).

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 14 May 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

