[In the past 24 hours, India (326 123), Brazil (84 486), the USA (37 916), and Argentina (27 363, have reported the highest numbers of cases. A global total of 12 546 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (late 12 May 2021 to late 13 May 2021). Countries reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (8 countries) include India, Brazil, the USA, Argentina, Colombia (16 581), Turkey (11 394), Germany (10 247), and Iran (10 145). A total of 53 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 25 of the 53 countries are from the European region, 8 are from the Americas region, 8 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 6 are from the South East Asia region, 4 are from the Western Pacific region, and 2 from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have decreased by 9.6%, while daily reported deaths have decreased by 3.0%. Similar comparative 7-day averages in the USA show a 15.7% decrease in daily reported cases and 6.7% decrease in reported deaths.

Impression: The global daily reported approximately 700 000 newly confirmed infections in the past 24 hours with over 162.52 million cumulative reported cases and over 3.37 million reported deaths. - Mod.UBA]
